  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "When releasing a proyect, we're trying to provide the artifact and the interface, for the users to be able to deploy and run tests on their local network (without releasing the source code).\r\n\r\nDeployed contracts work fine, but the errors received are no longer **CustomErrors**, but `Transaction reverted without a reason string` from a `<UnrecognizedContract>.<unknown>`.  So developers running tests will not be able know what's wrong with their test scenario.\r\n\r\nIs there a way of providing the artifact and the interface (containing the CustomErrors) and make the feature work as expected?",
